Sure - you'll need to install the wasm32-unknown-unknown target:

 
{code:java}
rustup target add wasm32-unknown-unknown --toolchain nightly
{code}
 

and then run cargo build for the target:

 
{code:java}
cargo build --target wasm32-unknown-unknown
{code}
The disted 2.0 version builds great for WASM - I tested it using [wasm-pack|https://github.com/rustwasm/wasm-pack] which seems like the most idiomatic way to build a Rust->WASM library these days. However, the latest version on master has the ability to read dictionary batches, hence the need to install from Git. Thanks for taking a look at the issue!
